<p>When selecting a solar installer in San Antonio, prioritize companies with proper Texas licensing, NABCEP (North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners) certification, and extensive local experience. Look for installers who are familiar with CPS Energy's interconnection requirements and local building codes specific to Bexar County. Top-quality installers should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels), workmanship (minimum 10 years), and performance guarantees. Request multiple quotes and verify each company's Better Business Bureau rating, online reviews, and references from recent San Antonio installations. Reputable installers will conduct thorough site assessments, provide detailed proposals showing expected energy production based on your roof's orientation and local weather patterns, and handle all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork with CPS Energy.</p>

